```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Agent as Sending Agent
    participant Transport as A2aTransport
    participant Router as MessageRouter
    participant Handler as MessageHandler
    participant Registry as AgentRegistry

    Agent->>Transport: send_message(A2aMessage)
    activate Transport

    Transport->>Transport: validate_origin()
    Transport->>Transport: validate_routing()

    Transport->>Router: route(message)
    activate Router

    Router->>Router: find_handler(message_type)
    Router->>Handler: handle_message(message)
    activate Handler

    Handler->>Handler: validate_payload()
    Handler->>Registry: query_capabilities(target_agent)

    Registry-->>Handler: Capabilities
    Handler-->>Router: HandlerResult

    Router-->>Transport: A2aResponse
    deactivate Router

    Transport->>Transport: update_session(session_id)
    Transport-->>Agent: Response
    deactivate Transport
```

## Description
A2A message processing flow from receipt through routing to handler execution and response.

## Key Steps
- **Step 1**: Agent sends message via A2aTransport
- **Step 2**: Transport validates origin and routing metadata
- **Step 3**: MessageRouter selects appropriate handler by message type
- **Step 4**: Handler validates payload and queries agent capabilities
- **Step 5**: Response propagates back through router with session update
